#. type: Title -
#: Interactive_Router.adoc:89
#, no-wrap
msgid "Laying out tracks"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Interactive_Router.adoc:95
msgid ""
"To activate the router tool press the _Interactive Router_ button image:"
"images/route_icon.png[Interactive Router Button] or the *X* key.  The cursor "
"will turn into a cross and the tool name, will appear in the status bar."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Interactive_Router.adoc:100
msgid ""
"To start a track, click on any item (a pad, track or a via) or press the *X* "
"key again hovering the mouse over that item. The new track will use the net "
"of the starting item. Clicking or pressing *X* on empty PCB space starts a "
"track with no net assigned."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Interactive_Router.adoc:106
msgid ""
"Move the mouse to define shape of the track. The router will try to follow "
"mouse trail, hugging unmovable obstacles (such as pads) and shoving "
"colliding traces/vias, depending on the mode. Retreating mouse cursor will "
"cause the shoved items to spring back to their former locations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Interactive_Router.adoc:110
msgid ""
"Clicking on a pad/track/via in the same net finishes routing. Clicking in "
"empty space fixes the segments routed so far and continues routing the trace."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Interactive_Router.adoc:113
msgid ""
"In order to stop routing and undo all changes (shoved items, etc.), simply "
"press **Esc**."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Interactive_Router.adoc:118
msgid ""
"Pressing *V* or selecting _Place Through Via_ from the context menu while "
"routing a track attaches a via at the end of the trace being routed. "
"Pressing *V* again disables via placement. Clicking in any spot establishes "
"the via and continues routing."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Interactive_Router.adoc:122
msgid ""
"Pressing */* or selecting _Switch Track Posture_ from the context menu "
"toggles the direction of the initial track segment between straight or "
"diagonal."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Interactive_Router.adoc:126
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Note**: By default, the router snaps to centers/axes of the items.\n"
"Snapping can be disabled by holding *Shift* while routing or selecting\n"
"items.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title -
#: Interactive_Router.adoc:128
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting track widths and via sizes"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Interactive_Router.adoc:137
msgid ""
"There are several ways to pre-select a track width/via size or to change it "
"during routing: - Use standard Kicad shortcuts. - Press *W* or select "
"_Custom Track Width_ from the context menu to type in a custom width/via "
"size. - Pick a predefined width from the _Select Track Width_ sub-menu of "
"the context menu. - Select _Use the starting track width_ in the _Select "
"Track Width_ menu to pick the width from the start item (or the traces "
"already connected to it)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title -
#: Interactive_Router.adoc:139
#, no-wrap
msgid "Dragging"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Interactive_Router.adoc:145
msgid ""
"The router can drag track segments, corners and vias. To drag an item, click "
"on it with *Ctrl* key pressed, hover the mouse and press *G* or select _Drag "
"Track/Via_ from the context menu. Finish dragging by clicking again or abort "
"by pressing __Esc__."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title -
#: Interactive_Router.adoc:147
#, no-wrap
msgid "Options"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Interactive_Router.adoc:151
msgid ""
"The router behavior be configured by pressing _E_ or selecting _Routing "
"Options_ from the context menu. It opens a window like the one below:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Interactive_Router.adoc:153
msgid "image:images/en/router_options.png[Screenshot]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Interactive_Router.adoc:155
msgid "The options are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Interactive_Router.adoc:158
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Mode* - select how the router handles DRC violation (shoving, walking\n"
"around, etc.)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Interactive_Router.adoc:161
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Shove vias* - when disabled, vias are treated as un-movable objects\n"
"and hugged instead of shoved.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Interactive_Router.adoc:165
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Jump over obstacles* - when enabled, the router tries to move\n"
"colliding traces behind solid obstacles (e.g. pads) instead of\n"
"\"reflecting\" back the collision\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Interactive_Router.adoc:170
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Remove redundant tracks* - removes loops while routing (e.g. if the\n"
"new track ensures same connectivity as an already existing one, the old\n"
"track is removed). Loop removal works locally (only between the start\n"
"and end of the currently routed trace).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Interactive_Router.adoc:174
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Automatic neckdown* - when enabled, the router tries to break out\n"
"pads/vias in a clean way, avoiding acute angles and jagged breakout\n"
"traces.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Interactive_Router.adoc:177
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Smooth dragged segments* - when enabled, the router attempts to merge\n"
"several jagged segments into a single straight one (dragging mode).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Interactive_Router.adoc:180
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Allow DRC violations* (__Highlight collisions__ mode only) - allows\n"
"to establish a track even if is violating the DRC rules.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Interactive_Router.adoc:185
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Optimizer effort* - defines how much time the router shall spend\n"
"optimizing the routed/shoved traces. More effort means cleaner routing\n"
"(but slower), less effort means faster routing but somewhat jagged\n"
"traces.\n"
msgstr ""
